# GitHub Project Board — never verify membership, never re-add

## Context

PipeWatch uses **two separate status systems**:
- **GitHub issue state** (`open`/`closed`) — driven by commit messages (`fixes #N` on `main`). Agents never modify this directly.
- **Project board Status** (Backlog / Ready / In Progress / In Review / Done / Closed / Declined) — managed via GraphQL `updateProjectV2ItemFieldValue`.

**Board Status is what matters.** Verifiers set Done on the board; the issue stays open until the commit lands on `main`.

| Board | Value |
|---|---|
| Org | `mdg-labs` |
| Repo | `pipewatch` |
| Project | **PipeWatch Roadmap** (Projects v2, project number: **5**) |
| Project node ID | `PVT_kwDODv-LLc4Ba3QP` |

## Blocking dependencies

A task depending on `#N` is **unblocked** when `#N`'s board Status is **Done** or **Closed** — regardless of GitHub issue state.

| Board Status | GitHub issue state | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| Done | `open` | Verified on `staging` — **unblocks dependents** |
| Closed | `closed` | Commit landed on `main` via release |

**Never** check GitHub issue `open`/`closed` to resolve dependencies — check **board Status**.

## Rule

**NEVER check whether an issue is already in the GitHub project.** Every issue created in this repo is automatically on project **#5**. Do not query, verify, or re-add.

## Forbidden

- **`gh project item-list`** — paginates unnecessarily; membership is guaranteed.
- **GraphQL membership checks** — `projectItems` is only valid for getting the **project item ID** to set Status.
- **`addProjectV2ItemById`** after issue creation — creates duplicates.
- **Any "verify issue is in project" step** in prompts or skills.

## Correct workflow for setting Status

1. **Get project item ID** via GraphQL (filter `project.number == 5`):
   ```bash
   gh api graphql -f 'query=query {
     repository(owner:"mdg-labs",name:"pipewatch") {
       issue(number:N) {
         projectItems(first:10) {
           nodes { id project { number } }
         }
       }
     }
   }'
   ```

2. **Set Status** via GraphQL mutation — see `.cursor/skills/orchestrator/github-board.md` for hardcoded IDs.

## Anti-patterns

```bash
# NEVER — checking membership
gh project item-list 5 --owner mdg-labs --format json | jq '...'

# NEVER — re-adding after creation
addProjectV2ItemById(...)

# CORRECT — get item ID and set Status
gh api graphql -f '...'  # updateProjectV2ItemFieldValue
```
